## Add "Exclude unmapped" and "Include excluded" bulk actions to mapping designer

Context: The mapping toolbar previously only allowed excluding/including items one at a
time via the context menu or side panel. When a domain has many unmapped entities or
relationships, clearing them in bulk required repetitive right-click interactions.
The backend `POST /mapping/exclude` already accepted a list of URIs, so the gap was
purely frontend — a toolbar-level bulk action was missing.

Changes:

1. src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-design.js
   Added `excludeAllUnmapped()`: collects all class and property URIs with no mapping
   entry and not already excluded, sends them in bulk to `POST /mapping/exclude`
   (`excluded: true`), updates local `MappingState` in-place, and refreshes the graph.

2. src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-design.js
   Added `includeAllExcluded()`: collects all class and property URIs currently marked
   `excluded`, sends them in bulk to `POST /mapping/exclude` (`excluded: false`),
   removes the `excluded` flag from local state, and refreshes the graph.

3. src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-design.js
   Exposed both functions on `window` (`window.excludeAllUnmapped`,
   `window.includeAllExcluded`) so the inline `onclick` handlers in the template work.

4. src/front/templates/partials/mapping/_mapping_design.html
   Added two toolbar buttons after the Refresh button: "Exclude unmapped"
   (`btn-outline-warning`, eye-slash icon) and "Include excluded"
   (`btn-outline-success`, eye icon), separated from the view controls by an existing
   `<div class="vr">` divider.

Modified files:
- src/front/static/mapping/js/mapping-design.js
- src/front/templates/partials/mapping/_mapping_design.html

